---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Terms of Service — SocialProof" noIndex={false}>
  <main style="padding:60px 0 100px;">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:780px;">
      <h1 style="font-size:36px;font-weight:800;margin-bottom:8px;">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p style="color:var(--text-muted);margin-bottom:48px;">Last updated: January 2025</p>
      <div style="font-size:17px;line-height:1.75;color:#374151;">
        <h2 style="font-size:22px;font-weight:700;margin:32px 0 12px;">Acceptance</h2>
        <p>By using SocialProof, you agree to these terms. If you don't agree, don't use the service.</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:22px;font-weight:700;margin:32px 0 12px;">The service</h2>
        <p>SocialProof provides tools for collecting, moderating, and displaying customer testimonials. We offer a free tier and paid plans.</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:22px;font-weight:700;margin:32px 0 12px;">Your content</h2>
        <p>Testimonials submitted through your SocialProof widget belong to you and your customers. You are responsible for ensuring you have permission to collect and display testimonials.</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:22px;font-weight:700;margin:32px 0 12px;">Prohibited use</h2>
        <p>You may not use SocialProof to collect fake testimonials, spam customers, or violate any law. We may suspend accounts that violate these terms.</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:22px;font-weight:700;margin:32px 0 12px;">Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p>SocialProof is provided "as is." We are not liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of the service.</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:22px;font-weight:700;margin:32px 0 12px;">Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions? Email <a href="mailto:team@socialproof.dev" style="color:var(--brand);">team@socialproof.dev</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
